text: This is a great scale for the price  I use it a few times a week to monitor weight loss  gain I have confidence knowing that it is consistent and dependablebr br The weight takes about 5 seconds to register  the numbers fluctuates within 1 pound when stepping on and you must remain still until the number on the display starts blinking  At that point you can step off of the scale and the number remains on the display for about 20 seconds  Stepping back onto the scale after the display turns black then results in the same reading almost every time  Also no need to tap a foot onto the scale to wake it up  Just stand on it and remain motionless and wait for the readingbr br Another thing I like about this scale is the width and length  Im 6234 with size 12 feet that are wide  I dont have an issue with foot space width of the scale or covering the display when standing on it  Ive never once felt like I was swaying  going to tip over and Ive never had an issue with accidentally stepping to close to a corner  side of the scale and had it tip over  meaning the rubber feet underneath are nice and close to the corners making for good stabilitybr br I use this on a hard tile floor so I cant speak for use on carpet or softer materials  Also it doesnt have bluetooth or wifi connectivity  those things didnt matter to me I was looking for size a nice display and consistency  If these are qualities you are looking for as well as a good price point this scale is a great choice

text: I have upgraded my review to from 3 4 stars  After wearing the watch for about three weeks I have become more sensitized to vibrating alarm while Im awake  It alerts me during most daytime activites  It still doesnt work as a wakeup alarm for me  However I have found the vibration is much more audible when it lays on my deskbr br The charge lasted almost a week on its first chargebr br The company noted if worn constantly the watch strap could irritate the skin I found that to be true  Although I didnt get a visible reaction my wrist felt uncomfortable  If I take it off at night it seems to help  Also I now wear mine as a loose bracelet but still have to take it off occasionally  Im hoping with time alarm watches will be upgraded to  be more user friendlybr br Pros  Light weight larger text in portrait mode long charge easy charging preview of next alarm setting inactivity alarm  Works with my Iphone 6s phonebr br Cons I bought this watch to use it for multiple reminders  My first attempt with the app I downloaded the wrong app  Look for its Icon  as well as the app name  For one not familiar with electronic watches the app was not intuitive The online videos are for older models The small manual is printed in minimicro print  The online app setup is very limited in versitilitybut what can you expect for 20 bucksbr br The unfortunate part of this watch is that the vibration alarm isnt strong enough nor does not repeat long enough to wake me up or alert me if Im working under deep concentrationbr br My fitbit had a strong enough vibration to wake me up  It repeated the alarm if I did not wake up right away to turn it off  Unfortunately my fitbit did not allow me to set muliple alarms through out the daybr br So Ill use this watch during my waking hours during light duty work  Ill be searching for another watch that meets my needs

title: Perfect scale to match any decor Practical
text: If youre looking for a fitness tracker but dont want to shell out the dough for the name brands this is a great alternate option You can sync it to your phone and it will notify you of calls  you cant answer them on the watch You can also read but not reply to text messages on the device and you can choose whether to get updates from some social media options toobr br As for the fitness tracker side of things it is pretty accurate as a pedometer Ive tested it out in comparison to other pedometers and they are very close You can set goals through the free app for how many steps you want to achieve miles you want to walk activity level timeframes sleep time The heart rate function is also pretty accurate  I have a wrist cuff blood pressure monitor that tests heart rate and this watch is within a point or two every time of the blood pressure monitors readingbr br The sleep function can be a little finicky depending upon how you sleep Since the screen is a double tap to activate if you are like me and sleep with your arm under your face you can sometimes activate the screen and take it out of sleep mode during the nightbr br The fit and comfort of the watch is pretty good My wrists are a little bigger than average and I still have a couple of notches of room on the band Ive not had any degradation to the band so its pretty durablebr br The app does have some quirks Ive loaded it on an Apple device and on an Android device It works well with both  but for some reason when it syncs my data on the Apple device it tends to load the steps up 10k higher than they were  for example which in turn make the calorie calculator show that Ive burned through more calories in a day than I would take in over the course of a month It tracks the miles accurately so I can forgive the steps  and the alerts triggered through the watch ignore the app loading things up higher so you receive alerts at your actual targets rather than 10 minutes into the day

title: The best hair vitamins thus far
text: Ive bought this brand of AlphaGPC before but never got the urge to test its claim of being stabilized against heat and moisture Being stabilized also renders it more bioavailable which is of course a good thing So tonight I emptied a cap onto a paper plate and placed the paper plate directly on top of a portable oil heater the type that looks like the old fashioned steam heaterradiators many people still have in their older homes Once the heater got really hot several hundred degrees easy I placed the paper plate with the little mound of AlphaGPC powder on it and covered it with another paper plate upside down on top of the first one After 45 minutes I removed the top paper plate and took a look The GPC had not altered in shape or consistency and remained the little pile of fine powder Which is exactly what stabilized alphaGPC is supposed to look like under very hot conditions and exposed to air This GPC passes the test 100 and I therefore obviously recommend it for passing this test plus the fact that Ive used it for some time now and I can tell my short and long term memory are both functioning quickly and smoothly and without any effort Add the fact that there are no excipients or fillers and there are a whopping 120 caps per bottle and I dont know of a better deal on the market There is another brand that has 120 caps per bottle and is cheaper but I gave it the same heat test as this one and it failed miserably Their stabiliized GPC obviously wasnt so I dropped that brand like a hot potato
